						<summary>

						<p>Stone set up in a field called Dāsaṇṇa-<hi rend="italic">gadde.</hi></p>						

						<p>[Dēvarāya II], 1440-41 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This badly damaged record is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1363</hi> (current), <hi rend="bold">Raudri, ba. 10, Sunday,</hi> the name of the month being lost. The year corresponds to <hi rend="bold">1440-41 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>It seems to register a gift to a deity for burning a perpetual lamp. etc., and refers to a <hi rend="italic">daṇṇāyaka.</hi> All details are lost.</p>						

						</summary>
